Part 1

library(ggplot2)
df <- read.csv("../../data/clean_data.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

total_killed <- sum(df$Total.killed, na.rm = TRUE)
total_wounded <- sum(df$Total.wounded, na.rm = TRUE)
total_kidnapped <- sum(df$Total.kidnapped, na.rm = TRUE)

event_stats <- data.frame(
  Category = c("Killed", "Wounded", "Kidnapped"),
  Count = c(total_killed, total_wounded, total_kidnapped)
)

event_stats$fraction <- event_stats$Count / sum(event_stats$Count)

# 创建饼图
p <- ggplot(event_stats, aes(x = "", y = Count, fill = Category)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", width = 1) +
  coord_polar(theta = "y") +
  labs(title = "Event Statistics Distribution") +
  theme_void() +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c('red', 'orange', 'yellow')) +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5) 
  ) +
  geom_text(
    aes(label = paste(Category, "\n", Count, " (", scales::percent(fraction), ")", sep = "")),
    position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5),
    color = "black"
  )

p
ggsave(
  file = "../../visualization/part1.2.jpg", 
  plot = p,
  width = 6,
  height = 6
)

# Read the cleaned data
df_clean <- read.csv("../../data/clean_data.csv", stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

# Aggregate data by country and year
country_year_data <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Country, Year) %>%
  summarize(
    incident_count = n(),
    affected_total = sum(Total.affected, na.rm = TRUE),
    killed_total = sum(Total.killed, na.rm = TRUE),
    wounded_total = sum(Total.wounded, na.rm = TRUE),
    kidnapped_total = sum(Total.kidnapped, na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = 'drop'
  )

# Select the top 20 countries with the most incidents
top_countries <- country_year_data %>%
  group_by(Country) %>%
  summarize(total_incidents = sum(incident_count)) %>%
  arrange(desc(total_incidents)) %>%
  slice_head(n = 20) %>%
  pull(Country)

# Filter data to include only top countries
filtered_data <- country_year_data %>%
  filter(Country %in% top_countries)

# Create the heatmap
plot2.1 <-ggplot(filtered_data, aes(x = Year, y = reorder(Country, -incident_count), fill = affected_total)) +
  geom_tile() +
  scale_fill_viridis(name = "Affected People", option = "inferno", direction = -1) +
  labs(
    title = "1997-2025 Time Heatmap",
    subtitle = "Affected People Count",
    x = "Year",
    y = "Country"
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = seq(1997, 2025, by = 3),  # Display years every 3 years
    labels = seq(1997, 2025, by = 3)   # Show every 3rd year as a label
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
    legend.position = "right",
    plot.title = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(size = 12)
  )

library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)

# Aggregate data by year and event type
area_data <- df_clean %>%
  group_by(Year) %>%
  summarize(
    Deaths = sum(Total.killed, na.rm = TRUE),
    Injured = sum(Total.wounded, na.rm = TRUE),
    Kidnapped = sum(Total.kidnapped, na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  pivot_longer(
    cols = c(Deaths, Injured, Kidnapped),
    names_to = "event_type",
    values_to = "count"
  )

# Create a stacked area chart
plot2.2 <-ggplot(area_data, aes(x = Year, y = count, fill = event_type)) +
  geom_area() +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c("Deaths" = "#FF8C00", "Injured" = "#FFD700", "Kidnapped" = "#FF0000"),
    name = "Event Type"
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "Humanitarian Security Event Type Trends (2007-2025)",
    x = "Year",
    y = "Affected Individuals"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom",
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold")
  )

part3

library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)

my_colors <- c("Deaths" = "#c45259", "Injured" = "#f6771d", "Kidnapped" = "#ff878b")
org_pct <- df_clean %>%
  select(UN, INGO, ICRC, NRCS.and.IFRC, NNGO, Other, Total.killed, Total.wounded, Total.kidnapped) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(UN, INGO, ICRC, NRCS.and.IFRC, NNGO, Other), names_to = "Organization", values_to = "Present") %>%
  filter(Present == 1) %>%
  group_by(Organization) %>%
  summarise(
    Deaths = sum(Total.killed, na.rm = TRUE),
    Injured = sum(Total.wounded, na.rm = TRUE),
    Kidnapped = sum(Total.kidnapped, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(Deaths, Injured, Kidnapped), names_to = "IncidentType", values_to = "Count") %>%
  group_by(Organization) %>%
  mutate(Total = sum(Count), Percent = round(Count / Total * 100, 1)) %>%
  ungroup()

plot3.1 <- ggplot(org_pct, aes(x = reorder(Organization, -Total), y = Count, fill = IncidentType)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  geom_text(
  aes(label = ifelse(Organization %in% c("INGO", "NNGO", "UN") & Percent > 5,
                     paste0(Percent, "%"), "")),
  position = position_stack(vjust = 0.5),
  size = 3,
  color = "white"
)+
  scale_fill_manual(values = my_colors) +
  labs(
    title = "Who Faces the Greatest Risk?",
    subtitle = "Proportion of Deaths, Injuries, and Kidnappings by Organization (1997–2025)",
    x = "Organization",
    y = "Number of People Affected",
    fill = "Incident Type"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

org_cols <- c("UN", "INGO", "ICRC", "NRCS.and.IFRC", "NNGO", "Other")
gg_attack <- df_clean %>%
  select(Means.of.attack, all_of(org_cols)) %>%
  filter(!is.na(Means.of.attack), Means.of.attack != "") %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = all_of(org_cols), names_to = "Organization", values_to = "Present") %>%
  filter(Present == 1) %>%
  group_by(Organization, Means.of.attack) %>%
  summarise(Count = n(), .groups = "drop") %>%
  group_by(Organization) %>%
  mutate(Percent = Count / sum(Count) * 100)

plot3.2 <- ggplot(gg_attack, aes(x = Organization, y = Percent, fill = Means.of.attack)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "fill") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent) +
  labs(title = "Proportion of Attack Types Faced by Organization",
       x = "Organization", y = "Proportion", fill = "Means of Attack") +
  theme_minimal()

plot3.2

library(ggraph)
library(ggplot2)

org_cols <- c("UN", "INGO", "ICRC", "NRCS.and.IFRC", "NNGO", "Other")

motive_net_data <- df_clean %>%
  select(Motive, all_of(org_cols)) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = all_of(org_cols), names_to = "Organization", values_to = "Present") %>%
  filter(Present == 1, !is.na(Motive), Motive != "") %>%
  group_by(Motive, Organization) %>%
  summarise(Count = n(), .groups = "drop") %>%
  mutate(from = Motive, to = Organization) %>%
  select(from, to, Count)

nodes <- tibble(name = unique(c(motive_net_data$from, motive_net_data$to))) %>%
  mutate(type = ifelse(name %in% org_cols, "Organization", "Motive"))

graph <- graph_from_data_frame(motive_net_data, vertices = nodes, directed = FALSE)

plot3.3 <-ggraph(graph, layout = "fr") +
  geom_edge_link(aes(width = Count), color = "#f6771d", alpha = 0.4) +
  geom_node_point(aes(color = type, size = degree(graph)), show.legend = TRUE) +
  geom_node_text(aes(label = name), repel = TRUE, size = 3.5) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Organization" = "#1f77b4", "Motive" = "#ff7f0e")) +
  scale_size(range = c(3, 8)) +
  labs(title = "Motives Behind Attacks on Humanitarian Organizations",
       color = "Node Type", size = "Connection Strength") +
  theme_void()

Part4

library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(ggplot2)
org_cols <- c("UN", "INGO", "ICRC", "NRCS.and.IFRC", "NNGO", "Other")

org_risk <- df_clean %>%
  select(all_of(org_cols),
         Nationals.killed, Nationals.wounded, Nationals.kidnapped,
         Internationals.killed, Internationals.wounded, Internationals.kidnapped) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = all_of(org_cols), names_to = "Organization", values_to = "Present") %>%
  filter(Present == 1) %>%
  mutate(
    National = Nationals.killed + Nationals.wounded + Nationals.kidnapped,
    International = Internationals.killed + Internationals.wounded + Internationals.kidnapped
  ) %>%
  group_by(Organization) %>%
  summarise(
    National = sum(National, na.rm = TRUE),
    International = sum(International, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(National, International), names_to = "WorkerType", values_to = "Count") %>%
  group_by(Organization) %>%
  mutate(Percent = Count / sum(Count) * 100)

plot4.1 <-ggplot(org_risk, aes(x = Organization, y = Percent, fill = WorkerType)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "fill") +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("National" = "#403619", "International" = "#68edcb")) +
  labs(title = "Who Takes the Risk? National vs International Staff by Organization",
       x = "Organization", y = "Proportion of Affected Staff", fill = "Worker Type") +
  theme_minimal()

plot4.1
ggsave(
  file = "../../visualization/part4.1.jpg", 
  plot = plot4.1,
  width = 6,
  height = 6
)
